items.title: Microsoft remakes Windows for an era of autonomous AI agents
items.summary: Microsoft is restructuring its Windows operating system to become what executives call the first "agentic OS . It embeds the infrastructure needed for autonomous AI agents to operate securely at enterprise scale . The shift is Microsoft's most significant architectural evolution of Windows since the introduction of the modern security model . With Windows running on an estimated 1.4 billion devices globally, it will likely shape how organizations deploy autonomous AI systems .

items.title: Writer's AI agents can actually do your work—not just chat about it
items.summary: Writer is launching a unified AI agent platform designed to let any employee automate complex business workflows without writing code . The platform combines chat-based assistance with autonomous task execution in a single interface . Users can use natural language to instruct the AI to create presentations, analyze financial data, generate marketing campaigns, or coordinate across multiple business systems like Salesforce, Slack, and Google Workspace .

items.title: Google Antigravity introduces agent-first architecture for asynchronous, verifiable coding workflows
items.summary: Google launches Antigravity, an agent-first coding agent platform . It lets developers create agents that can execute complex tasks automatically . The platform is powered by Gemini 3 and Anthropic’s Sonnet 4.5 models . Google says it built the platform with four key tenets — trust, autonomy, feedback, and self-improvement — which sets it apart from other coding platforms .

items.title: Microsoft’s Agent 365 shifts AI agents from sandbox tools to enterprise-grade infrastructure
items.summary: Microsoft launches Agent 365, the control plane for AI agents . The company says the platform “delivers unified observability” through telemetry, dashboards, and alerts to track every agent in use . Microsoft's approach stands out because it bundles what’s usually a patchwork of add-on tools into a single, governed control plane . Agent 365 treats agents as parts of the stack, giving IT and security teams unified oversight .

items.title: Investing in America 2025
items.summary: Google’s deep investments in American technical infrastructure, R&D and the workforce will help the U.S. continue to lead the world in AI, Google says . Google's deep investments will help American tech companies continue to develop and compete in artificial intelligence, the company said in a new blog post on Monday . Google says it is investing in the American workforce and infrastructure to develop AI technology .

items.title: New ways to plan travel with AI in Search
items.summary: AI Mode search bar can help you plan a trip with the help of AI Mode . AI Mode searches can also be used to help people plan their travel plans . The search bar is a result of the AI Mode feature that lets users plan their own trips with AI Mode enabled to search for travel destinations in AI Mode mode . For more information, visit CNN.com/Travel.com and iReport .

items.title: Google is committing $2.25 million to support AI-ready data in Africa.
items.summary: New funding from Google will help launch a regional Data Commons for Africa . New funding will help create a regional data Commons for African countries . Google says it will help build a data Commons in Africa for African nations . Google: Africa's Data Commons will be a Data Commons in the region, Africa's biggest source of data and source of information .
